{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_16","type":"command_execution","command":"/usr/bin/zsh -lc \"tail -n 120 'human-intervention-logs/io.confluent:kafka-schema-registry-client:8.2.1/library-preparation-preflight/pi-generation-2026-06-23T23-26-06-818193Z.log'\"","aggregated_output":"     * so operations on one scope will never affect another.\n     *\n     * @param scope Identifies a logically independent Schema Registry instance. It's similar to a\n     *              schema registry URL, in that two different Schema Registry deployments have two\n     *              different URLs, except that these registries are only mocked, so they have no\n     *              actual URL.\n     * @return A client for the specified scope.\n     */\n    public static SchemaRegistryClient getClientForScope(final String scope) {\n      synchronized (SCOPED_CLIENTS) {\n        if (!SCOPED_CLIENTS.containsKey(scope)) {\n          SCOPED_CLIENTS.put(scope, new MockSchemaRegistryClient());\n        }\n      }\n      return SCOPED_CLIENTS.get(scope);\n    }\n  \n    /**\n     * Get a client for a mocked Schema Registry. The {@code scope} represent\n[recv] {\"type\": \"message_start\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_J6103N0Ui4pNrldAu3lBPLSN|fc_0bbd08e7bc65c7d7016a3b15ea7f508196b8707f6bd585a118\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"\\n validateAndMaybeGetMockScope 6115\\nk slate.\\n   * @param scope Identifies a logically independent Schema Registry instance. It's similar to a\\n   *             schema registry URL, in that two different Schema Registry deployments have two\\n   *             different URLs, except that these registries are only mocked, so they have no\\n   *             actual URL.\\n   */\\n  public static void dropScope(final String scope) {\\n    synchronized (SCOPED_CLIENTS) {\\n      SCOPED_CLIENTS.remove(scope);\\n    }\\n  }\\n\\n  public static void clear() {\\n    synchronized (SCOPED_CLI