 output should be a single JSON object, and I’ll note that no environment properties are necessary.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"{\\n  \\\"action\\\": \\\"no_action\\\",\\n  \\\"summary\\\": \\\"The artifact resolves with its normal runtime dependencies, including Avro, Kafka clients, Jackson, Guava, HttpClient, and Confluent common-utils. Meaningful client coverage is reachable without Docker or extra dependencies because the jar includes MockSchemaRegistryClient and MockSchemaRegistry with the mock:// pseudo-protocol for in-memory schema registry testing.\\\",\\n  \\\"deterministic_setup\\\": [],\\n  \\\"agent_guidance\\\": \\\"No environment variables or system properties are required. Prefer the built-in MockSchemaRegistryClient or MockSchemaRegistry mock:// scope for registry operations instead of requiring a live Schema Registry service.\\\",\\n  \\\"risks\\\": [\\n    \\\"Tests that choose CachedSchemaRegistryClient against a real http:// endpoint would need a running Schema Registry, but the library provides an in-memory mock specifically to avoid that for tests.\\\",\\n    \\\"JSON Schema or Protobuf-specific provider coverage may require separate Confluent provider artifacts, but Avro schema/client coverage is available from this artifact's declared dependencies and is sufficient for meaningful coverage of this coordinate.\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\", \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0bbd08e7bc65c7d7016a3b15fca55c8196aee7795bc93273c9\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"oca/gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 559, \"output\": 744, \"cacheRead\": 27136, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 28439, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 1782257136622, \"responseId\": \"resp_0bbd08e7bc65c7d7016a3b15f142288196826e41b1f87ce9ce\"}, \"toolResults\": []}\n[recv] agent_end\n[send